    public class Log
extends MovableActor

    Log

    The Log class is used to create the Log object.

    A Log object is set in Map. It can move with the constant speed as time goes on. In each frame, this object also check the wall touch and check whether there are animal intersect with it. When it touches the Frog, it will ask GameController to handle some consequences.

    Note: This class extends MovableActor abstract class and implements MovableActor.act(long) and MovableActor.checkTouch().

    从以下版本开始:

    • 构造器详细资料

      • Log

        public Log​(java.lang.String imageLink,
           int size,
           double xpos,
           double ypos,
           double s)

        The constructor of Log class to generate instance

        This constructor sets the Log in the given position x and y in the Map. Set the constant speed in the given speed. Set the initial image with the given size.

        参数:
        imageLink - The path of image needed to be set to Log
        size - The size of the image
        xpos - The position of x in the Map where digit stays
        ypos - The position of y in the Map where digit stays
        s - The speed of Log movement

    • 方法详细资料

      • act

        public void act​(long now)

        This method will do the following tasks: 1. move the Log 2. check whether Log has touched the right or left wall 3. check whether Log has touched the Frog

        This method that will be called by ActAnimation in every frame to execute all above tasks.

        指定者:
        act 在类中 MovableActor
        参数:
        now - The current time of calling method.

      • checkTouch

        public void checkTouch()

        This method checks whether Log has touched the Frog and call GameController to handle consequences.

        When the Log is intersected with Frog, it will call GameController.handleLogTurtleTouched(MovableActor)

        指定者:
        checkTouch 在类中 MovableActor
